{
  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "Fix Icon Visibility Issue - White Icon on White Background\n\nResolve the visibility problem where icon-accent elements are displaying white icons on white backgrounds, making them invisible to users.\n\nRequirements:\n- Identify all instances of icon-accent components with this issue\n- Determine appropriate background color or icon color for proper contrast\n- Ensure minimum WCAG contrast ratio of 4.5:1 for accessibility\n- Apply consistent styling across all icon-accent usage\n- Test in both light and dark themes (if applicable)\n- Verify changes don't break existing visual design patterns\n\nEdge cases to consider:\n- Icons in different states (hover, active, disabled)\n- Icons on various background contexts (cards, headers, sidebars)\n- System theme preferences that might affect color rendering",
  "title": "Fix icon-accent contrast for accessibility compliance",
